<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-01-20T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-01-20T17:00:00-05:00" n="650" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d650">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">820.7961 Dept. of Commerce Flight/13:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in Bolivia</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Cottrell</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-01-20T17:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">January
                                            20, 1928—5 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>2. Department’s No. 1, January 7.<note n="90" xml:id="d650fn90">See
                                    footnote 86, <ref target="#pg_811">p. 811</ref>.</note>
                                Department of Commerce states that Duke Banks is local
                                representative of the Curtiss Airplane and Motor Corporation and
                                desires Legation and Consulate to cooperate with him in promoting
                                interest in American aircraft products and aeronautics in Bolivia.
                                Please comply and inform Consulate.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>